        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-05 20:44:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(8 inline comments)\n\nMain change is to have lustre_errno_{ntoh,hton}() take a negative argument and return a negative errno, and only convert the argument/return for the LDLM code that uses a positive argument.\n\nNote that there is also some HSM code that is using a positive error value - hsm_progress_kernel.hpk_errval.  I'm not sure if it is passed over the network, but if yes it needs to be swabbed as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
